== About Me

I'm a fourth-year PhD student in the [https://www.essie.ufl.edu/civil-coastal-engineering Department of Civil and Coastal Engineering], [http://www.ufl.edu/ University of Florid], , majoring in Transportation Engineering (Please find my lab [https://faculty.eng.ufl.edu/sermos-lab here]). I received my bachelor degree in Transportation Engineering from [https://en.swjtu.edu.cn/ Southwest Jiao Tong University], Chengdu, China, where I was advised by [https://faculty.swjtu.edu.cn/yanghongtai/en/index.htm Prof. Hongtai Yang]. Before joining UF, I was a visiting research assistant at [https://shanghai.nyu.edu/ New York University Shanghai], Shanghai, China from 2020 to 2021, where I was advised by [https://shanghai.nyu.edu/academics/faculty/directory/zhibin-chen Prof. Zhibin Chen].

My research mainly focuses on the applications of data science (e.g., data analytics and machine learning) on travel behavior and evacuation behavior.

== Education
- Ph.D. in Transportation Engineering, University of Florida, January 2021 -- present.
- B.E. in Transportation Engineering, Southwest Jiaotong University, September 2016 -- June 2020.

== Recent News

~~~
- *May 15th 2024* Our latest work entitled "Travel Demand Forecasting: A Fair AI Approach" is published in IEEE Transactions on Intelligent Transportation Systems!
- *Mar. 4th 2024* Our latest work entitled "Modeling Protective Action Decision-Making In Earthquakes By Using Explainable Machine Learning and Video Data" is published in Scientific Reports!

~~~

